original_title: Don Quishocking: Wij Zijn Volstrekt in de War
overview: In the last theater show (1981) of the Dutch cabaret company Don Quishocking, the internal dispute is central. When George Groot returns from Pune, it appears that he has joined the Bhagwan movement. All group members deal with it in their own way, but it seems inevitable that the group members have grown apart.
title: Don Quishocking: We Are Utterly Confused
